<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 19 at 8:48AM EST  by NWS Cleveland</headline>
<description>...A line of snow showers will affect southern Portage...Mahoning...
southeastern Medina...northern Stark and southern Summit Counties
Until 945 AM EST....
At 848 AM EST, radar indicated snow showers along a line extending
from near Hubbard to Medina, moving east at 50 mph.
HAZARDS INCLUDE...
Winds to 40 mph...
Visibility dropping to less than half of a mile...
Locations impacted include...
Akron, Canton, Youngstown, Medina, Salem, Columbiana, Cuyahoga Falls,
Boardman, Kent, Barberton, Green, Alliance, Wadsworth, Tallmadge,
North Canton, Louisville, Campbell, Canfield, Sebring and Mogadore.
Use extra caution if you must travel. Rapid changes in visibility and
potentially slick roads may lead to accidents.</description>
